title: Feedback Report on Documented Life-Sustaining Treatment Decisions in CLC
- The report includes data only for Veterans who were newly admitted to your CLC
in the last 6 months, month by month.
- Data comes from the LST template in CPRS. Only templates with answers for all
- If a Veteran had more than one LST template completed in a month, only the first
- Each Veteran was counted only once per month even if they had multiple stays.
- Veterans are defined as either long stay or short stay residents, based on their
treating specialty; those admitted for hospice are counted as long stay residents.
